text: The Napa Valley was shaken at 2 : 09 a. m. Thursday by a magnitude 4. 6 earthquake located near Clearlake in Lake County, the U.S. Geological Survey reported.  The temblor rattled homes in Napa, but would not have been expected to do any local damage.  The USGS rates 4. 6 magnitude as a "light"quake.  Two aftershocks, magnitude 2. 9 and 2. 2, occurred immediately following.
title: Lake County earthquake shakes Napa.
